quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,26,"Eat and drink, and be glad. And if you see any human being, say, ‘I have vowed silence<sup>7</sup> to the Most Compassionate, so I will not talk to any human being today.’”","[7] Sawm: literally means to abstain or fast from food, speech, etc."
  19,27,"Then she came to her people carrying him. They said, “O Mary, you have committed something monstrous!",""
  19,28,"O sister of Aaron,<sup>8</sup> your father was not a man of evil, nor was your mother unchaste.”","[8] Aaron was a pious man at the time of Mary, or she was from the descendants of Aaron, Moses’ brother."
  19,29,"Thereupon she pointed to him. They said, “How can we talk to someone who is still a baby in the cradle?”",""
  19,30,"Jesus said, “I am a slave of Allah. He has given me the Scripture and made me a prophet.",""
  19,31,"He has made me blessed wherever I may be, and has enjoined upon me prayer and zakah as long as I am alive,",""
  19,32,"and has made me dutiful to my mother, and has not made me an oppressor or disobedient.",""
  19,33,"Peace is upon me the day I was born, the day I will die and the day I will be resurrected.”",""
  19,34,"Such was Jesus, son of Mary – a word of truth about which they are in doubt.",""
  19,35,"It is not befitting for Allah to beget a son. Glory be to Him<sup>9</sup>! When He decrees a matter, He only says to it, “Be,” and it is.","[9] i.e., far exalted is He above any such need."
  19,36,"[Jesus said], “Indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. This is a straight path.”",""
  19,37,"But the factions differed among themselves<sup>10</sup> [about him]. So woe to the disbelievers from the scene of a momentous Day!","[10] Some believed that Jesus was God or the son of God, whereas those who truly followed him considered him only as Allah's messenger."
  19,38,"How sharp they will hear and see on the Day they come to Us! But today the wrongdoers are clearly misguided.",""
